comments: Morant (MEM) makes marginal contact with Green's (LAC) right arm during rebounding.
Beverley (LAC) briefly has his arm around Valanciunas' (MEM) midsection before correcting.
Harrell (LAC) makes marginal contact to the front of Morant (MEM) that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Harrell (LAC) establishes himself in a screening position in Crowder's (MEM) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Morant (MEM) makes marginal contact with Harrell's (LAC) right arm as he goes up to the basket.
Harrell (LAC) briefly places a hand on Morant (MEM) during his driving shot attempt, but the contact is marginal.

Crowder (MEM) makes marginal contact with George's (LAC) backside after the release of the jump shot attempt, and then incidental contact with George's head as they each attempt to retrieve the ball. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Morant (MEM) makes marginal contact with George (LAC) at the start of his dribble and does not affect his SQBR.
Morant (MEM) fails to establish position in the frontcourt within eight seconds.
Green (LAC) legally contests Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) jump shot attempt.
George (LAC) is already in Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) path when contact occurs in the lane, which George does not deliver.
Harrell (LAC) establishes himself in a screening position in Crowder's (MEM) path and does not deliver the contact.
Green (LAC) and Jackson Jr. (MEM) engage and disengage during the rebound.
Hill (MEM) makes marginal body contact with Williams (LAC) during his drive to the lane.
Hill (MEM) brings his hand down and makes contact to Williams' (LAC) left wrist after his gather, affecting his driving shot attempt.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) establishes his left foot as his pivot after receiving the pass, which he maintains along the sideline as he stays in bounds.
Valanciunas (MEM) and Harkless (LAC) briefly engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
When Morant (MEM) releases the throw-in, Harkless (LAC) deflects it and the clock correctly runs to 00:00.0.
